  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounts & HR Assistant",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Who we are?</strong></h3><p>For the Love of Laundry is Singapore's leading premium non-toxic laundry and dry-cleaning provider. We are looking for a dedicated, self-initiated and detail-oriented Accounts & HR Assistant with a minimum of 2 years of relevant experience. The ideal candidate should have basic knowledge and hands-on experience in accounting processes and HR operations. Training will be provided.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><p><u>Finance & Accounts:</u></p><ol><li>Maintain daily accounting entries.</li><li>Prepare and issue customer invoices.</li><li>Prepare and coordinate payments to suppliers and other payees.</li><li>Manage petty cash, expense claims, and receipt verification.</li><li>Prepare reports.</li></ol><p><u>HR:</u></p><ol><li>Prepare and process payroll, including salary calculations, incentives/OT and deductions.</li><li>Support recruitment, onboarding, work pass administration, and off-boarding processes.</li><li>Apply, renewal and cancellation of work pass</li><li>Assist with HR functions such as employee records, attendance, and leave management.</li><li>Maintain proper documentations.</li></ol><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ol><li>Minimum 2 years of experience in HR and/or Accounts.</li><li>Working experience with accounting and/or HR software.</li><li>Experience in payroll preparation.</li><li>Good team player with good communication and time-management skills.</li><li>Able to work independently with minimal supervision.</li></ol><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><p>Relevant qualifications in Commerce, Accounting, HR, or a related field.</p><p>Training and OJT will be provided for this role to familiarize you with our processes.</p><p><strong>Job Work Duration: </strong>Monday to Friday physically in office, 9am to 6pm.</p><p><strong>Job Location</strong>: 17 Soon Lee Road, Singapore 628080.</p>",
